The paper deals with multi-label learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper proposes a method to incorporate structured semantic correlations to solve the missing label problem of multi-label learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with image annotation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
